## Linked native libraries

### FFTW (FFTW3, single precision)
License: **GPL** (the version Tempo builds and links — `libfftw3f`). See the
FFTW upstream project for terms. Used by `libft1` for the FFT routines
(`four2a` and related DSP). On the Linux/WSL2 cross build it is statically
linked from a MinGW-built `libfftw3f.a`; on native MSYS2 builds it is located
via `pkg-config`.

### Boost (header-only CRC)
License: **Boost Software License 1.0** (SPDX: `BSL-1.0`). Only the
**header-only** `<boost/crc.hpp>` is used, by `libft1`'s `crc14.cpp`. No
compiled Boost library is linked.

